The Cinnamon Scented Incense has energized your inner Sim.
Those were some crazy visualization techniques!
Hmmm...those self esteem exercises seemed pretty good.

Razor-focused after hearing those cognitive focusing methods.

Deliciously sweet, and deceptively good for you.

{0.SimFirstName} has been struck with an infatuating aroma. Love is in the air (literally thanks to the Sandalwood).

No stress, no mess, no fuss, no worry. Such a relaxing rub.

Ok maybe it’s not that old, but older than your mom. The light from this lamp has seen the beginning of time and the start of electricity! This light piece will illuminate any home and its classic appeal will bring beauty to any room!

This one singular object combines the functionality of a lamp with the practicality of a column, all tied together with that unmistakable logo: yours. A staple of the Joose series, it makes a lovely centerpiece, end piece, or in-between piece. Where does that logo go again? Here!

Vegan options available.

A metal strip that will feel right at home amongst your undoubtedly exquisite architecture.

Sometimes, all that’s needed is a Single Strip of Light to brighten up any room. And If one isn’t enough, that’s OK, you can always add more.

The sleek, modern, simplicity of this design will lighten any mood! It will brighten from the floor to the ceiling and keep out any bad ju-ju. The recessed lighting will leave you with so much room for activities!

This light is the perfect blend of style and functionality, just don't look at it directly.

Designed by a relative of Mondrian himself, this breathtaking simple design will knock your socks off! Or change them for you. Try on all your outfits! Be formal and hang out in the backyard or sit around your house in your new workout gear. Those yoga pants are great for lounging!

Always trying to stir up drama, this mirror displays your Sim in the most unflattering way possible no matter how he or she looks at it.

This is not a mirror for gazing into. NO! This is a mirror for basking in your awe inspiring magnificence. Break your other mirrors, they are nothing to you! You can handle the bad luck! Stomp upon their pieces beneath your boots, of course you own boots, big heavy boots. Now scream “ARGH!” You’ve never looked better.

For those long walks down a dark alley in the middle of the night, this is the best...wait, why are you walking down dark alleys in the middle of the night?
A stylish and elegant home decor accent piece. Perfect for holding flowers, garden trimmings, creating an interesting nook in your lot... or just to say you own a giant vase.

In an attempt to go out of business to spite their evil investors, Zzbrft started selling giant blocks of concrete as sitting furniture. Yet despite Zzbrft's best attempts to destroy their business, consumers continue to flock to stores to pick up this uncomfortable sitting apparatus. Undeterred, Zzbrft is currently considering renaming this item to "Please stop buying me".
Why would anyone sit on this? By Zzbrft

We had 8 2x4s. We cut 4 of them into 1/3rds. We threw away 4 of the 1/3rds. We glued the other 8 1/3rds to the remaining 4 2x4s. We then nailed the 8 1/3rds to those 4 2x4s. We then stained the 4 2x4s, and the 8 1/3rds, but before that we sanded them, and then we stained them. We then sat upon our creation. It collapsed. We did it all again, but added 8 brackets to keep the 8 1/3rds from collapsing. It worked. The Simple Ottoman, ready, steady, for you.

This firm couch, defined by its sharp lines and blocky structure, is a place of respite for the sore posterior. Like an outcropping in the wilderness, be it a tree stump, or rock smoothed by windswept time, The Posterior’s Respite is a retreat for the seekers of comfort.

The Artificial Fever Room will help your Sim with some steam therapy. Relax on the redwood benches and enjoy the steam from 1,000 year old lava rocks. Walls sold separately. But batteries are included!

StoneZone brings you an all new take on the classic sauna. Constructed out of heat-resistant stones that remain cool even at high temperatures, this sauna is one that won't scald Sims' bottoms when they sit down.

The Slick Beats, the first in the revolutionary audio design from DJ Sudoku and crew, is a machine that promises no bad sounds marred by distortion, crackles or technical goblins outside of the artists’ intent. Slick Beats will soothe your ears and cure your soul in a way that renders the songs on its airways into truly sublime art.
Let the music overtake you and wash away the negative energy with the affirmative tunes that pour out of this speaker.
This is a wall-mounted stereo intended for use at community venues. Wash away the stress with the relaxing vibes of new age music.

Marvel at this masterpiece of man-made machined modernity. Its medium is not of mediocrity, but a meticulous manifestation of meditation and measure. Maximize the magnificence of molding in a mosaic of mahogany. Most majestic.

You know what’s awesome? An Awesome Cube! You know what’s more awesome? An Awesome Cube with an arbitrary break in its cubeness providing an aesthetic disharmony to your Awesome Cube viewing pleasure. You know what’s even more awesomer? You can put stuff on the Awesome Cube, because it’s an end table! Oh yeah.
With an abundance of austerity and a modicum of sophistication, this table fills a very specific furniture need.

Ancient texts indicate that inanimate objects, be they chairs, sculpture, or tables, have no soul. Their insides are empty and missing entirely. The renowned sculptor Claude X, in a daring riposte, charged this claim directly. The Hollow, a table with soul, stands without a center to mock scholars of archaic thought.
Following in the footsteps of the "Please Use Other Door" door, this toilet prefers Sims take their bladder needs elsewhere.

Sweating, grunting, and perspiring are neither posh nor glamorous. Every expression of energy of the foot hitting the treadpath is typically so degrading it wounds the very style of its occupant. The Sprint Chic cries foul. Beneath its smooth, rounded supports and elegant digital console, is a rubber belt of such exquisite style that running in place is now, and forevermore, haute couture.
Give mundanity the cold shoulder with this cool frosted glass window. It’s so stylish, it’ll give you chills.
A tiled window can often be the very piece you need to complete the feng shui of your household collection.
Looking for a way to bring your room up to modern speed? This clear window will enable aesthetic mode in crisp fashion.

Tauted by manufacturer Sagan Tyson as "Definitely not a gateway to another time." This wall fixture still might impress. Even though it probably won't transport your Sim through time, it sure looks pretty.

Window flocking was hot in the 70s, but surprisingly fell out of favor due to a backlash against silhouette puppetry. Thankfully the art of window flocking was never lost, and along with advances in silhouette dimming technologies, the flocking window industry is on the verge of booming once again.

Windows man... they let you see like stuff and things. They’re so transparent… it’s like you can just be part of everything. But this window man… it’s meta. It’s like they took the world and made it all fuzzy. It’s a fuzzy world man.
What's there to say? It’s a window. It lets light in and keeps the cold out.
Let the sunshine while keeping the negative energy out with these positive wooden windows.

Through narrow slats, each meticulously crafted by indubitable industrial designer Claude X, eyes can peer and see the world anew. With fresh design comes fresh perspectives. What more is a window, than a perspective?

Exhale. Feel it. Whisper the count aloud to yourself. One more rep. Pull it down. Push it. Do you feel it? How about now? Where does it hurt? While your mind asks these important questions, everyone around you is gawking at the gorgeous machine upon which you’re perched. With enough work? They’ll gawk at you as well.

A Sim that acquires wellness is a Sim that can regulate their moods and sensations as they sway through the gales of life's enduring dilemmas.\n\nWellness is primarily increased through Meditation, Yoga, and Massages. Increasing this skill will unlock new Yoga poses, massage types, and some transcendent meditation techniques!

The Wellness skill allows your Sims to perform various massages, do Yoga poses, give wellness advice to other Sims, and create healthy recipes.\n Sims gain Wellness skill by meditating, doing Yoga, giving massages, and other relaxation-related actions.
At high Wellness skill your Sim can unlock special powers like levitating and teleporting!

There’s a bunch of new objects in The Sims 4 Spa Day Game Pack that help boost Wellness Skill. Try using any of them found in the Spa Items build mode sort! You can even build your very own sauna room using the Artificial Fever Room object.

A Yoga Class takes place at every Spa venue that has an Instructor Zen Again Yoga Mat on it. Different Yoga Classes occur regularly through the day. When one is about to start your Sim will receive a notification from the Yoga Instructor letting them know that a class will start soon.\nYou can click on the Yoga Instructor’s portrait in the notification to find out where they are and join the class!

The Instructor Zen Again Yoga Mat has a special footprint that allows it to be placed with other objects. Place other Zen Again Yoga Mats in the special footprint to make your very own Yoga Class! Only mats that are in the Instructor Mat’s footprint will be included in the Yoga Class.
You can make your own Yoga Class at any Spa venue. If your current venue type is set as Spa, the Instructor Zen Again Yoga Mat will be available in the Spa Items sort.
